15—17. A man who can reckon up all the interruptions to sleep at Rome, could tell the number of the hands that are raised to olash vessels and instruments of brass when an eclipse is seen.

The custom alluded to is that of mising adin with cymbals, or brazen vessels of all sorts when an eclipse of the moon took place. The belief on which this custom was founded was that an eclipse was caused by magieians, who had power by means of ineantations to pull the moon out of the heaven. They raised this noise, therefore, to prevent the moon hearing the incantations, and so to counteraot the evil power.
